Zomato Data Analysis Project
Overview
This project is an Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) of the Zomato dataset, focusing on uncovering insights about restaurants, cuisines, ratings, and customer preferences. The project uses Python and its libraries for data analysis and visualization, aiming to support data-driven decisions in the food delivery and restaurant industry.

Objectives
The primary objectives of this project are:

Understand the distribution of restaurants across different cities.
Analyze the ratings and reviews to assess customer satisfaction.
Identify the most popular cuisines and restaurants.
Examine the cost and price trends in the restaurant industry.
Discover key insights to assist stakeholders in improving business strategies.
Tools and Libraries Used
Python for programming
Pandas for data manipulation
NumPy for numerical operations
Matplotlib and Seaborn for data visualization
Jupyter Notebook (or any IDE you prefer)

Data Cleaning:

Removing duplicates and missing values.
Standardizing columns and data formats.
Handling outliers where applicable.
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):

Visualizing distributions of ratings, costs, and reviews.
Analyzing geographical distribution (e.g., restaurants by city).
Identifying trends and patterns in cuisines and ratings.
Visualization:

Bar Charts: Top cuisines, cities, and restaurant chains.
Heatmaps: Correlation between ratings, reviews, and cost.
Pie Charts: Share of restaurants by cuisine type.
Key Findings and Conclusion:

Documented insights from the analysis.
Recommendations for businesses based on the findings.
